Wildflower painting of Red Grevillea

Ellis Rowan1900

Museum of Applied Arts and Sciences
Sydney, Australia

Watercolour wildflower painting, Grevillea banksii (Red Spider Flower), watercolour on paper, by (Marian) Ellis Rowan, Australia, c. 1900. Watercolour and gouache painting of Grevillea banksii depicting red/pink flowers, bud and foliage on greenish wash background.

Details

  • Title: Wildflower painting of Red Grevillea
  • Creator: Ellis Rowan
  • Date: 1900
  • Location: Queensland, Australia
  • Physical Dimensions: 575mm (h) x 406 (w)
